    <description>Adult patients with chronic rhinosinusitis who failed treatment with antibiotics and topical corticosteroids and underwent endoscopic sinus surgery. Preoperative evaluation included paranasal sinus CT scans. The diagnosis was confirmed by endoscopic examination showing purulent and/or mucopurulent discharge in the middle and/or superior meatus.</description>
