  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Patients with chronic rhinosinusitis whose uncinate process had to be removed to enable
        surgical access to the sinuses.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Patients with chronic rhinosinusitis who:

          -  Failed conservative medical treatment.

          -  Stopped treatment (topical or systemic corticosteroids) at least two months before
             endoscopic sinus surgery.

          -  Had a Lund-MacKay CT score of 2 and higher of 24 available.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Immunosuppressed patients.

          -  Patients in whom a pathologic evaluation of the middle turbinate was necessary (e.g.,
             suspected neoplastic disorder).

          -  Patients with a Lund-MacKay CT score &lt; 2 of 24 available.

          -  Pregnant women.

          -  Patients who underwent prior endoscopic sinus surgery.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
